				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The new version (1.0.3) of Advanced Textual Confirmation (ATC) is a next step in making a better tool. Changes:
<br />

<br />
1) The protection now can be attached not only at the top level, but also inside functions. As result, more fine-grained control is possible. Here is an example, using ATC with phpBB3: <a href="http://www.phpbb.com/community/viewtopic.php?p=3025581#p3025581" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://www.phpbb.com/community/viewtopic.php?p=3025581#p3025581</a>.
<br />

<br />
2) The language pack is started. The current translations:
<br />

<br />
* Czech, French, German, Polish, Spanish: <a href="http://hakin9.org/en/haking.html" target="_blank" class="postlink">Haking9 magazine</a>
<br />
* Russian: <a href="http://uucode.com/blog/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Oleg Parashchenko</a>
<br />

<br />
